<item>
            <title>[TIKA-3810] Vtt file (encoding UTF-8 with BOM) seen as text/plain</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3810</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Vtt file created on Windows (UTF-8 &lt;ins&gt;with BOM&lt;/ins&gt;) is incorrectly detected as &lt;em&gt;text/plain&lt;/em&gt; type and it should be &lt;em&gt;text/vtt&lt;/em&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The application using Tika and where the file is uploaded for mime type detection is an Unix machine.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The vtt file is passed as inputstream to the Tika&apos;s default detector (we don&apos;t want to detect mime type by the file extension).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please find attached the vtt file that Tika is detecting as text/plain .&lt;/p&gt;</description>
